		<h2 class='content__hed miller-banner-regular'>Caretakers</h2>

		<p class='content__body'>During the 1970’s, most parks and common areas were almost beyond repair amidst social upheaval across the city. Since that time, the parks and their monuments have been revitalized by The Friends of the Public Gardens, and currently cost one million a year to maintain, with $100,00 on parks and 42 different sculptures. For more information or to donate to help the restoration process, please visit <a class='shaw-link' href='http://friendsofthepublicgarden.org/join-donate/' target='_blank'>http://friendsofthepublicgarden.org/join-donate/</a>.</p>

